===Etymology 1===
From Old French [[tens]] (modern [[temps#French|temps]]), from Latin [[tempus]].

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# {{grammar}} Any of the forms of a [[verb]] which distinguish when an action or state of being occurs or exists. The basic tenses in English are present, past and future.  English also has [[perfect tense]]s ([[present tense|present]] perfect, [[past tense|past]] perfect and [[future tense|future]] perfect) and [[progressive tense]]s.

